OL,3,GGrampian
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA dry and bright start to the
OL,6,Fday but cloud bubbling up with showers
OL,7,Fdeveloping through the morning.
OL,8,FShowers will turn heavy and perhaps
OL,9,Fthundery later. Some bright or sunny
OL,10,Fspells between showers.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FHeavy and perhaps thundery
OL,13,Fshowers at first will gradually ease
OL,14,Fthrough the evening. It will then stay
OL,15,Fdry overnight with clear spells
OL,16,Fdeveloping.
OL,17,
OL,18,CThursday:FA dry and bright start but
OL,19,Fturning cloudy through the morning
OL,20,Fwith outbreaks of light rain spreading
OL,21,Fnorthwards in the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
